Hey Creator,

Thanks for reaching out to R√òDE! We're excited to connect with you and
can‚Äôt wait to see the incredible content you‚Äôll create using our
top-of-the-line microphones and audio gear. Trusted by professionals,
artists, and creators around the world, we‚Äôre here to support your creative
journey.

Whether you decide to produce a full video about R√òDE or include a brief
brand integration, the choice is entirely up to you. We value your creative
freedom and want you to make the content in your own unique style.

Just a quick reminder: The gear is yours to keep at no cost, and we‚Äôll also
compensate you for creating and sharing content that features our products.

Here‚Äôs how to get started:

Visit  https://rodecommunity.com , choose the gear that works best for your
project, and fill out the form with your shipping details.

After reviewing your request, one of our campaign managers will contact you
to confirm your gear selection, discuss your rates, and go over the
specifics of your video. You'll also have the opportunity to share your
rate card and finalize the payment details.

We‚Äôre excited to see your creativity in action and are thrilled to be part
of your content creation!

Looking forward to collaborating,
The R√òDE Team

Hope you're doing great! I'm Francis from Aha (formerly Head AI), an creator agency connecting creators with top campaigns worldwide. We're currently coordinating several collaboration opportunities that align well with your content, so I've combined them below for your convenience.

1. Storm MCP
Streamline your AI workflow with Storm MCP: a secure, enterprise-grade gateway that unifies LLMs, RAG data, and tools‚Äîseamless integration, real-time observability, and robust security.
‚Ä¢ One TikTok Video: 105 USD creator fee

2. YouArt
YouArt.ai is the first agentic creative workflow platform that allows users to generate complex workflow and high-quality videos and visual content through simple natural-language prompts.
‚Ä¢ One TikTok Video: 43 USD creator fee

Build full-stack apps in minutes with Zoer‚ÄîAI-powered, no-code, fully customizable, and ready for instant cloud deployment. Just describe your idea, and Zoer does the rest!

These rates are the default guideline prices displayed on the Aha platform. You're welcome to adjust your rates directly on the platform if you prefer.

We value long-term creator relationships and are expanding our roster of ongoing partners. If this collaboration works well, we'd welcome the chance to continue working together.

Kind regards,
Francis

subject: Re: A quick question...

triggerMessage.subject: Re: A quick question...
triggerMessage.body:
Hi Matt and team,

Massive fan of your work. Despite what some say in the YouTube and X comments I have really appreciated your pivot with AI Hero and the content you have been putting out. It makes sense given the context of what it currently means to be a software developer in my opinion, and the stuff you‚Äôve put out already about Typescript should keep most people including myself occupied for a while. 

I think despite the limitations of the transformer approach to LLMs etc, it‚Äôs evident that there is genuine utility in these models. Your recent video about using plan mode extensively and the tips from that have genuinely made a tremendous difference in the way I work. 

It is giving me more trust in what an LLM is putting out because of that initial planning/exchange. In the past I‚Äôve just given a series of prompts and Claude et al have basically ripped through with varying levels of success, so I had been feeling a bit bummed out despite the Opus hype until recently. 

Things like this I would love to learn more about!

Kind regards,
Tom

Best,

Sam Liu

Hi, Matt.

The thing that interests me the most with AI is exactly how to harness what
AI is supposed to be good at, while ensuring output is accurate,
deterministic, and consistently repeatable.

Being able to do this at scale from plans/tasks (from sprints) using
subagents, then validate and verify outputs still feels out of touch for me.

I "know" the rough idea of what is needed, but actually getting a fully
fleshed working example feels like a few obstacles too many.

I've learned a lot from reading your tweets and articles, but it's gluing
it all together that evades me.

triggerMessage.body:
Hey Matt Pocock team,

Really enjoyed your recent videos. Your breakdown of AI tools and how to
use them best is always spot on.

I'm reaching out from Composio <https://composio.dev/> about a partnership
opportunity around the Cowork launch.

As you know, Cowork is trending. We recently shipped *Open **Claude CoWork
(*https://github.com/ComposioHQ/open-claude-cowork*)*, an open-source take
on Claude Code. Most existing implementations (including others in OSS) are
essentially GUI or browser-based wrappers that automate tasks locally or
rely on browser automation for SaaS apps ‚Äî which gets slow and brittle.

What makes Co-Work different is that it comes *natively integrated with
800+ APIs* as composio manages the auth on backend. This means users can
not only automate desktop tasks, but actually complete real knowledge work
across tools like Linear, Slack, Jira, GitHub, etc. fast.

We‚Äôd love to collaborate on a dedicated video where you walk through
Co-Work and, in the process, explore why deep, API-level integrations
matter for agentic workflows.

The project‚Äôs getting strong organic traction already ‚Äî Julian Goldie and
Tom Doerr have both shared it recently ‚Äî and momentum is picking up
quickly. I have attached some example demos of its capabilities. Do you
think this will be a fit for your audience?

Would love to do a dedicated video this week.
Best,
Audery Graham
Composio <https://composio.dev/>

This is a module system issue, not a version problem. Your compiled JavaScript has export statements, but browsers need a module-aware script tag to understand them.
In your HTML file, change:
<script src="example.js"></script>
To:
<script type="module" src="example.js"></script>
The type="module" tells the browser to treat the file as an ES module, which supports import/export syntax.
If that doesn't match what the lesson expects, the alternative is changing your TypeScript compiler settings to output a different module format (like CommonJS or a bundled file), but adding type="module" to the script tag is the typical fix here.

subject: Re: A quick question...

triggerMessage.subject: Re: A quick question...
triggerMessage.body:
Hi Matt,

I am a Software Engineering Manager so I like to orchestrate and delegate
to AI like I would a team of engineers. I treat AI less like a chatbot and
more like a programmable collaborator. Lately, I've been trying to build a
system that produces reliable work on demand using specially designed
prompts, workflows, phase gates, and verifiable iteration loops. Since I'm
a hands-on learner, I've been building small, custom CLI tools with Effect
that I can compose together into reusable systems I use daily.

I'm interested in learning more about: controllability, repeatability, and
compounding leverage. What I want to learn the most: how to use Effect to
make AI outputs trustworthy enough to integrate into serious engineering
workflows without constant babysitting.

Thanks,
Urban

triggerMessage.subject: CollaborationÔºöLocal AI Supercomputer, 80GB RAM, Zero Token Fees
triggerMessage.body:
Hi there,

I'm Simon, hope you're doing great!

We've been following your content on *YouTube *for a while, and we really
love your take on* AI hardware/tech gadgets*.

We are reaching out from the team behind *Tiiny AI Pocket Lab*. We have
created the *world's smallest personal AI supercomputer*, officially
certified by *Guinness World Records*.


*About Tiiny:*

Tiiny is a pocket-sized AI supercomputer designed for privacy-first
computing. It runs massive LLMs (up to 120B parameters) fully offline at
blazing speeds of up to 40 tokens/s. Powered by the PowerInfer engine
(8.5k+ GitHub stars), it is the ultimate cost-effective lab for developers.

Tiiny functions as a drop-in replacement for cloud APIs, offering full
OpenAI compatibility for seamless integration into your current projects.
Acting as your personal *Token Factory, *You can freely develop and
experiment with your projects without worrying about unpredictable token
fees.

If you need a quick refresher, you can watch the TiinyOS and Tiiny API
walkthrough videos anytime at these links:

   - TiinyOS: https://youtu.be/YvNVk8cuxw8
   <https://l.gotourl.es/l/1d6715e48bb48f30ef8d7abf2ba2b272c5d8a088?u=13508529>
   - Using Tiiny as a token factory: https://youtu.be/zEnsrz2W5L4
   <https://l.gotourl.es/l/cc487777242e14470bb6624ac6cb4021322821ff?u=13508529>


We would love to invite you to create a *dedicated review of *the Tiiny AI
Pocket Lab.
*Please be advised:*

   1. We are targeting a campaign release by *March*. To ensure we can lock
   in a slot in your schedule for this timeline, we are happy to proceed with
   a *paid sponsorship.*
   2. Could you please share your rates for a dedicated video?
   Alternatively, if you have other collaborative ideas, we are open to
   hearing them!


Looking forward to hearing from you!

Best regards,
Tiiny AI Team

triggerMessage.body:
Hi Matt,

Longtime reader of your work on Twitter/X, but largely new to your more
organized education materials. As a frontend/full-stack dev with ~9 years
of professional experience in JS/TS/React/Node/Vercel/etc, I am always
looking for great sources to help me get better.

Your work has really spoken to me on multiple levels

   1. Your work around following and growing in this fast-paced era of AI
   engineering - it's daunting to keep up with everything that is changing,
   and not just use the ever-changing tools of the day, but *use them well*.
   Looking for quality, tested, focused changes I can make to my day-to-day
   workflow makes keeping up feel manageable, even exciting
   2. Leveling up in my fundamentals - I was a bootcamp grad, I have no
   formal CS training, and in my career in startups I've found that the focus
   is almost always entirely on shipping and not on learning the fundamentals.
   I often feel like I just sort of skipped past a lot of that, and now as I
   look to become a contributor worthy of senior/staff level, missing those
   foundations really matters. Typescript is an area where I know some
   technical growth can pay major professional dividends.

I'm really excited to dive more deeply into your work, as it seems like you
structure things in a very intentional way to have others learn.

Best,
Andrew

Great! If you're just starting out with TypeScript, I'd recommend beginning with the fundamentals:
**Start with the basics** - Learn how TypeScript differs from JavaScript, type annotations, interfaces, and basic types. Most learners find it helpful to work through exercises that show you how types prevent bugs.
**Practice incrementally** - Don't try to learn everything at once. Focus on types first, then move into more advanced concepts like generics, utility types, and advanced patterns once you're comfortable with the foundation.
Is there a specific area you're curious about, or would you like help navigating the Total TypeScript resources available?

- TypeScript is actually going to *add* to your skillset, not replace it. The demand for TypeScript skills is growing, not shrinking

triggerMessage.subject: üëã  Feedback from bradwebber@gmail.com about Total TypeScript
triggerMessage.body:
Hey Matt, I hope you‚Äôre well. I just watched your video titled ‚ÄúShip working
code while you sleep with the Ralph Wiggum technique‚Äù on YouTube. Thank you for
putting that together; it is fantastic. QQ: When you specify the number of
iterations, does that apply to a single item in your PRD or all items? In other
words, if your loop picks up a task and fails to implement that task, does the
next iteration in the loop pick up the failed task and try again, or does it
potentially pick another task? Perhaps another way to ask is: if you specify a
max-iterations of 10 but your PRD has 20 items, will your ralph loop stop after
implementing 10 items (assuming it implements each item successfully on its
first attempt)?

subject: Re: Paid collaboration with DevTools ‚Äî Modern API Testing Tool

triggerMessage.subject: Paid collaboration with DevTools ‚Äî Modern API Testing Tool
triggerMessage.body:
Hey Matt,

I really appreciate your content around developer workflows and tooling. We
think DevTools aligns well with those themes.

I‚Äôm reaching out from DevTools ‚Äî we built a Go-based API client that lets
you turn real browser traffic (HAR files) into replayable API flows. It‚Äôs
way faster than Postman and Bruno, and you can export everything as
readable YAML for version control and Git review.

DevTools is open source, works as both a CLI and a desktop app, and has a
visual builder for flow trees and reusable checks. It‚Äôs perfect for
developers and QA teams looking to speed up API testing and automate flows
in CI.

We‚Äôre running a paid promo for creators ‚Äî happy to discuss rates for a
sponsored feature or demo.

If you‚Äôre interested, let me know and I‚Äôll send over more details!

Thanks,
Mustafa

Hi,

I hope this message finds you well.

My name is CJ from SEI Marketing, and we are reaching out on behalf of
Pippit, an AI-powered website tool focused on improving efficiency and
productivity for digital users.

We are currently engaging select creators for an upcoming global campaign
and identified your content as highly aligned with Pippit‚Äôs positioning.
Your work in AI and productivity-focused content stands out as a strong
potential fit for this collaboration.

Proposed Deliverables:
One (1) video published on YouTube, Instagram, or TikTok (with preference
for YouTube and Instagram)
On-camera, real-person presentation with the creator‚Äôs face visible
A clear and authentic explanation or demonstration of Pippit

Usage Rights (Instagram & TikTok only):
30-day ad authorization code
Copyright authorization for paid media usage

If this opportunity is of interest, may we kindly ask for your current rate
or rate card for this type of collaboration? This will help us ensure
alignment before sharing the full campaign brief, timeline, and
collaboration details.

Thank you for your time and consideration. We look forward to the
possibility of working together.

Kind regards,
CJ
SEI Marketing

subject: Re: Hi Matt, loved your LLM,ML,Python video ‚Äî Let‚Äôs collaborate to build something cool with Milvus!

triggerMessage.subject: Hi Matt, loved your LLM,ML,Python video ‚Äî Let‚Äôs collaborate to build something cool with Milvus!
triggerMessage.body:
Loved your LLM,ML,Python video ‚Äî let‚Äôs collaborate to build something cool
with Milvus!

Hi Matt,

I‚Äôve been following your recent videos on *youtube*, and really enjoyed how
you break down complex AI workflows in such a clear and practical way. Your
audience‚Äôs interest in LLMs, RAG systems, and MLOps also aligns closely
with what we‚Äôre building at *Zilliz*
<https://zilliz.com?utm_source=email&utm_medium=kol_pitch&utm_campaign=p> ‚Äî
the team behind *Milvus* <https://github.com/milvus-io/milvus>, the world‚Äôs
most popular open-source vector database.

We‚Äôre currently exploring *paid collaborations* with leading creators to
boost awareness of Milvus and Zilliz, and to help developers learn how to
build smarter, more scalable AI search and retrieval systems. Our focus is
mainly on YouTube videos ‚Äî *hands-on explainers, tech deep dives, or
creative showcases* ‚Äî but we're also open to LinkedIn or X if you prefer
those formats.

Some content themes we‚Äôre especially excited about include:

   - *Building intelligent AI systems* ‚Äî showing how search, retrieval, or
   memory make agents more capable
   - *Scaling AI infrastructure* ‚Äî exploring performance, latency, and cost
   trade-offs as apps move from prototype to production
   - *Bridging data and AI* ‚Äî helping developers turn unstructured data
   into powerful context for LLMs

To help you get a quick sense of what we‚Äôre working on, here‚Äôs our
latest *Creator
Brief* with examples and technical resources:

üìÑ Open Creator Brief
<https://docs.google.com/document/d/18UDda1rEUSFbzcbJUIagw7XK7XzTFXCTmsGcHU587dA/edit?usp=sharing>

If this sounds interesting, I‚Äôd love to explore a collaboration. When you
reply, could you also share:

   - *Your current availability* ‚Äî any open slots in the next few weeks?
   - *Your typical production timeline* ‚Äî how long you usually need for
   scripting ‚Üí filming ‚Üí publishing
   - *Your preferred content angles* ‚Äî any topics above that excite you, or
   ideas you‚Äôd like to explore?
   - *Your rates or media kit* ‚Äî so we can align quickly

Looking forward to hearing from you,

Best,
*Bruce Chen*
Creator Partnerships Associate | Zilliz

[image: Zilliz √ó Milvus]

¬© 2025 Zilliz. This message was sent to selected creators for potential
collaboration opportunities.

subject: Re: Would you consider Metabase integration?

triggerMessage.subject: Would you consider Metabase integration?
triggerMessage.body:
Hey Matt, Margaret from Metabase here üëã

I recently came across your YouTube channel and think Metabase could be a
good fit for your audience.

Metabase is an open-source BI tool that lets you query and visualize
business data in minutes-no need to wrestle with SQL or set up something
heavyweight like Looker or Tableau. Just connect your production database
and go. It's fast, intuitive, and built for devs (45k+ GitHub stars
<https://github.com/metabase/metabase>).

Would you be open to integrating Metabase in one of your videos? If so,
what are your rates?

subject: Re: YouTube Collaboration Inquiry

triggerMessage.subject: YouTube Collaboration Inquiry
triggerMessage.body:
Hi Matt Pocock,

I'm Dhinesh from Syncfusion Software. I've been following your YouTube channel and really enjoyed your recent video-great work!
I'm reaching out to explore a potential collaboration to promote BoldSign<https://boldsign.com/>, a secure and developer-friendly eSignature solution. BoldSign offers comprehensive REST APIs and SDKs, making it easy for developers to integrate eSignatures into their applications.
Please check our API page - BoldSign eSignature API - Fast, Secure & Developer-Friendly<https://boldsign.com/esignature-api/>
Here's a quick overview of what BoldSign offers:

  *   Secure, legally compliant eSignature workflows
  *   Blazing-fast and scalable REST APIs
  *   SDKs available for .NET, Java, Node.js, Python, and Php
  *   Features like templates, audit trails, branding, and team management
You can check out our API documentation: Getting started - API Documentation - BoldSign<https://developers.boldsign.com/api-overview/getting-started/?region=us>
SDKs here: Integrate eSignatures into your app with ease by BoldSign(r) SDKs<https://staging.boldsign.com/electronic-signature-sdk/>
You can also check our BoldSign API overview video here -  BoldSign's Blazing Fast eSignature APIs<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cWvt44mM0eg&t=5s>
We believe your content and audience are a great match for BoldSign, and we'd love to explore a collaboration-whether it's a sponsored video, tutorial, or another creative format.
Let me know if you're interested, and I'd be happy to share more details!

Best regards,
Dhinesh
Syncfusion Software

Greetings,¬† 



I appreciate your response to our last note.¬†

I represent Skillshare ‚Äî a worldwide platform for online education where millions of students worldwide explore thousands of classes on almost any topic: from creative skills and business to personal growth and lifestyle.¬†



Your audience will be able to enjoy 1 month of access to Skillshare, while for you this is a clear and paid partnership with transparent terms. We‚Äôve previously collaborated with top creators on YouTube and TikTok and are open to new collaborations.¬†



Format of cooperation:¬†

‚Ä¢ Our main focus is an integration in one of your upcoming YouTube videos (30‚Äì90 seconds)¬†

‚Ä¢ Other options are also possible: short mentions, full dedicated reviews, or integrations on Instagram or TikTok¬†

‚Ä¢ A special promo code providing your audience with 1 month of free access¬†

‚Ä¢ We‚Äôll share all necessary materials and links beforehand to make preparation as simple as possible. If this collaboration appeals to you, we‚Äôll send a media kit for further details.¬†



Agreement details:¬†

‚Ä¢ This is a paid partnership ‚Äî we welcome your pricing and can provide partial prepayment if that‚Äôs easier¬†

‚Ä¢ Timing is open ‚Äî we‚Äôll fit your availability¬†

‚Ä¢ Your creative freedom is important to us, so the integration will remain organic.¬†



Please share your usual rates or media kit when convenient. After that, we‚Äôll prepare the paperwork and campaign materials.¬†

If you prefer, we can set up a quick Zoom call (10‚Äì15 minutes) to cover the details.¬†



Kind regards,

subject: Re: Test Request ‚Äî Running 120B LLMs locally on the World's Smallest Supercomputer

triggerMessage.subject: Test Request ‚Äî Running 120B LLMs locally on the World's Smallest Supercomputer
triggerMessage.body:
Hi there,

I'm Neko from *Tiiny AI*. I'm reaching out with something we think fits
your audience perfectly.

We have just officially certified by *Guinness World Record**s.*

*Tiiny AI Pocket Lab is the **world's **smallest **personal Al
supercomputer** that can run a**n* *up-to **120B LLM **fully offline** (testing
shows 21.14 tokens/s average **throughput** over 1-hour continuous
inference at 1K context length for 4bit GPT-OSS-120B.)**.*
[image: Guinness World Records.jpg]
Here are a few reports for reference:
Meet the World's Smallest 'Supercomputer' from Tiiny Al
<https://wccftech.com/meet-the-worlds-smallest-supercomputer-a-machine-bold-enough-to-run-120b-ai-models/>
Tiiny AI Reveals AI Pocket Lab Mini PC Powered by 12-core Arm CPU
<https://www.techpowerup.com/343905/tiiny-ai-reveals-ai-pocket-lab-mini-pc-powered-by-12-core-arm-cpu>
The world's smallest AI supercomputer is the size of a power bank
<https://www.digitaltrends.com/computing/the-worlds-smallest-ai-supercomputer-is-the-size-of-a-power-bank/?utm_source=twitter&utm_medium=socialorg&utm_campaign=rss-feed>

What might interest you more is *how we pulled this off.*
The attached diagram breaks down the stack ‚Äî *TurboSparse *+* PowerInfer* ‚Äî
the architecture enabling *20+ tok**ens**/s* at *~30W TDP* while keeping
full model intelligence.
[image: TurboSparse + PowerInfer.png]
PowerInfer isn't just experimental, it's already proven.

The project has *8.5k+ **GitHub <https://github.com/SJTU-IPADS/PowerInfer>*
* stars*, backed by active contributors and real‚Äëworld deployments.
We also included a PDF with more details if you want to dive further.
Why This Might Interest You
This is the first time you can run a *GPT-4o-level** model **locally*,
*privately *and* continuously*, on a device as small as a smartphone.

*Tiiny **AI **Pocket Lab features*:

   - Compute: SoC( Armv9.2 CPU + NPU ) 30TOPS & dNPU 160TOPS
   - RAM: 80GB LPDDR5X
   - Offline operation & dual-encryption for complete privacy
   - True long-term memory based on local knowledge base
   - Supports open-source LMs & open-source agents
   - Handy TiinyOS SDK for open development


It's essentially your *personal inference node*.
[image: Tiiny.jpeg]
Interested in Trying It Out?
We'd like to send you a unit *in exchange for one review video* sharing
your honest experience.
Are you available to receive a unit between *Jan 15* *‚Äì** Mar 6*?

If yes, please share shipping details (delivery 5‚Äì8 business days):

   - Name:
   - Phone Number:
   - Email:
   - Address:
   - City:
   - State:
   - Country:
   - Postcode:


If you have any questions, feel free to reach out anytime.

Best,

Neko
Tiiny AI Team

subject: Re: Google 3 Flash, available today

triggerMessage.subject: Google 3 Flash, available today
triggerMessage.body:
Following the launch of Gemini 3 Pro
<https://blog.google/technology/developers/gemini-3-pro-vision/>, today we
expanded the Gemini 3 Family and introduced Gemini 3 Flash, our newest
model built for speed and scale.

With Gemini 3, we introduced frontier performance across complex reasoning,
multimodal and vision understanding, and agentic and vibe coding tasks.
Gemini 3 Flash retains this foundation, combining Gemini 3's Pro-grade
reasoning with Flash-level latency, efficiency, and cost. It not only
enables everyday tasks with improved reasoning, but is also our most
impressive model for agentic workflows.

Starting today, Gemini 3 Flash is rolling out to millions of people
globally:

   -

   For developers in the Gemini API in Google AI Studio, Gemini CLI, our
   new agentic development platform Google Antigravity and other developer
   platforms
   -

   For everyone via the Gemini app and in AI Mode in Search
   -

   For enterprises in Vertex AI and Gemini Enterprise


Here is our media kit doc
<https://docs.google.com/document/d/1rdSQwm9HnewvmtRmEmY-sMR-2bgP335U7X6bSaMbRdQ/preview>
and assets
<https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1lUU-QE91LJCI5uVQcDnY-5HRcdOT5kLE?usp=sharing>,
with more information. You can also learn more in our Keyword blog post
<https://blog.google/products/gemini/gemini-3-flash/>.

If you‚Äôd like to stay up to date on Google's most important AI
announcements for developers, as well as exclusive content opportunities,
feel free to join our EMEA developer group on Signal
<https://signal.group/#CjQKIMfAIxUcZOg692gkqV1RyU2Lh9TVO00w2-2c2q4MkgpWEhA84Axbccc7Y1FFFuOXuyP4>
:

[image: image.png]

Please let me know if you have any questions as I would be more than happy
to help.
-- 

[image: OGB-INSIDER-BLOGS-GoogleLogox2-Animated (1).gif]

  ‚Ä¢  Billy Burnett

  ‚Ä¢ Google | 1-13 St Giles High St | London

  ‚Ä¢  Mobile: +44 (0)7789 485 937

  ‚Ä¢  Email: billyburnett@google.com

If you received this communication by mistake, please don't forward it to
anyone else (it may contain confidential or privileged information), please
erase all copies of it, including all attachments, and please let the
sender know it went to the wrong person. Thanks!

Hello, this is Tia from the Proactor AI team. We‚Äôve previously discussed a
potential collaboration.

During the third round of creator outreach, we noticed that our budget was
too low, which affected creators‚Äô willingness to work with us. After
internal discussions, we have increased our collaboration budget and
officially launched the fourth phase of our global promotion plan.

In the testing phase, we developed a high-conversion video script that
helped a creator achieve over 1 million views and 5,000+ new user
registrations with a single video. We are now inviting experienced creators
to replicate this success.

<https://proactor-ai.jmailroute.net/x/d?c=49121671&l=2525ae92-5e6b-48cd-a047-68f7a007aca0&r=1cb23678-d14e-40b8-9861-52a64017e7f6>

   *$300 per video*, settled weekly (*$1,500 per week*).

   Monthly performance bonuses will be granted based on account growth. Rates
   are negotiable‚ÄîI am happy to help outstanding creators apply for higher
   commissions.

If you‚Äôre available and interested this week, I can immediately send the
updated collaboration plan.
We look forward to working together again and creating the next viral hit!

Additionally, for identity verification, you may confirm through Proactor
AI‚Äôs official email: *support@proactor.ai <support@proactor.ai>*.
Best regards,
Tia

‚Ä¢ Multi-Agent Workflows: Deploy a personal ‚Äúdev team‚Äù of AI agents to tackle different tasks simultaneously.

Sherry
